sistant text before a tool call, keep it short and use it to update the world model. Helpful optional prefixes are `World model:`, `Goal model:`, `Action model:`, `Recent findings:`, `Open questions:`, `Plan:`, and `Cross-level notes:`.\nWhen calling `python`, emit exactly the tool-call format shown elsewhere in this prompt for this model. Use only that format; do not add markdown fences, prose wrappers, or alternate tool-call syntax. Do not quote or place tool-call markup inside explanatory text; when you decide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 2: you have used 34 of about 58 target actions so far.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "Interesting! After UPx3 and SPACE:\n- Before SPACE: blue (24-27, 20-39), left red (16-19, 8-19), right red (24-27, 28-39)\n- After SPACE: left red (16-19, 8-19), right red (24-27, 20-27), blue (24-27, 28-39)\nSo SPACE caused:\n1. The right red block to shrink from (24-27, 28-39) to (24-27, 20-27) - it moved left!\n2. The blue to move from (24-27, 20-39) to (24-27, 28-39) - it moved right!\nWait, actually the right red block was at (24-27, 28-39) before, and now it's at (24-27, 20-27). So the right red block moved from cols 28-39 to cols 20-27. And the blue moved from cols 20-39 to cols 28-39.\nSo SPACE caused the blue and the right red block to swap positions! The blue was at cols 20-39 (overlapping with right red at cols 28-39), and after SPACE, the blue is at cols 28-39 (where the right red was) and the right red is at cols 20-27 (where the blue was, but shifted).\nWait, let me re-read:\n- Before SPACE: blue (24-27, 20-39), right red (24-27, 28-39)\n- After SPACE: right red (24-27, 20-27), blue (24-27, 28-39)\nSo the blue was at cols 20-39 (20 cols wide), overlapping with the right red 